What are the processing methods of connector pins?
The pin structure of the connector is designed based on the static or low-speed environment of the connector, so the position of the pin structure of the connector is fixed during connection, while the running speed of the motor car or subway is very high, so the vibration is also very large. The pin structure of the connector designed to adapt to the static or low-speed environment cannot adapt to the high-speed environment, when the EMU or subway is running at high speed, the radial and axial displacement deviation occurs at the connection of the connector, which is easy to cause poor contact of the connector.
2023/08/08
Can RJ11 plug RJ45 module
RJ11 can be inserted into the RJ45 module, but can not be used. Because RJ11 is a 6-pin connector and RJ45 is an 8-pin connector, it can be plugged in and cannot be used.
The RJ45 crystal head is a connector with 8 grooves and 8 contacts (8p8c), while the RJ11 crystal head usually has only 6 grooves and 4 contacts (6p4c). Therefore, the volume of the RJ45 crystal head is larger than that of the RJ11 crystal head. The RJ11 crystal head can usually be inserted into the RJ45 interface, but not vice versa, but it is strongly recommended not to use the RJ11 crystal head for the RJ45 interface.

What are the processing methods of connector pins?
The pin structure of the connector is designed based on the static or low-speed environment of the connector, so the position of the pin structure of the connector is fixed during connection, while the running speed of the motor car or subway is very high, so the vibration is also very large. The pin structure of the connector designed to adapt to the static or low-speed environment cannot adapt to the high-speed environment, when the EMU or subway is running at high speed, the radial and axial displacement deviation occurs at the connection of the connector, which is easy to cause poor contact of the connector.
Can RJ11 plug RJ45 module
RJ11 can be inserted into the RJ45 module, but can not be used. Because RJ11 is a 6-pin connector and RJ45 is an 8-pin connector, it can be plugged in and cannot be used.
The RJ45 crystal head is a connector with 8 grooves and 8 contacts (8p8c), while the RJ11 crystal head usually has only 6 grooves and 4 contacts (6p4c). Therefore, the volume of the RJ45 crystal head is larger than that of the RJ11 crystal head. The RJ11 crystal head can usually be inserted into the RJ45 interface, but not vice versa, but it is strongly recommended not to use the RJ11 crystal head for the RJ45 interface.
